    "body": "### Problem\n\nI can't stand my work being interrupted by hit-enter, this is the single major annoyance I have with nvim. Right now I do something like this:\n```lua\n\t\tbequiet = function(msg, log_level, opts)\n\t\t\tprint(string.sub(tostring(msg), 1, vim.v.echospace))\n\n\t\t\tlocal log = io.popen(\"systemd-cat -t nvim\", \"w\")\n\t\t\tlog:write(tostring(msg))\n\t\t\tlog:close()\n\t\tend\n\n\t\tvim.notify = bequiet\n\t\tvim.api.nvim_out_write = bequiet\n\t\tvim.api.nvim_err_write = bequiet\n```\nThis redirects all the errors to system journal. But I still get popups occasionally, and it maddens me as I have no idea where else to look at to suppress it all.\n\nMaybe there's a way to disable like all messages for good? I don't mind losing useful info just not to get hit-enter interrupted. Thanks!\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nSingle entry-point to disable interruptions.",
